!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

foremost /ˈfɔːˌməʊst/

1. ADJ The foremost thing or person in a group is the most important or best. 最重要的; 最好的 

例： He was one of the world's foremost scholars of ancient Indian culture. 他是世界上最优秀的古印度文化学者之一。 

2. PHRASE You use first and foremost to emphasize the most important quality of something or someone. 首先 [强调] 

例： It is first and foremost a trade agreement. 它首先是一项贸易协定。

</div>

